            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
              <tr> 
                <td class="chblue"><font class="h1font"> Intermediate Decks</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Raging Inferno V 1.0</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size=1>(3.75)</font> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=24532">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=11817">Howard "Riusaldregan" Brody</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=11817&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Cald spells and creatures to burnout your opponent.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> July 21, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Magi :<br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(376)">Barak</a> the Red<br>
Starting : <a href="javascript:card_browser(359)">Arbolit</a>, Flame <a href="javascript:card_browser(404)">Rudwot</a>, <a href="javascript:card_browser(393)">Thermal Blast</a><br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(378)">Grega</a><br>
Starting : <a href="javascript:card_browser(359)">Arbolit</a>, <a href="javascript:card_browser(679}<a href="javascript:card_browser({378)">Grega</a>&#39;s Ring</a><br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(677)">Vorga</a><br>
Starting : <a href="javascript:card_browser(359)">Arbolit</a>, <a href="javascript:card_browser(675)">Smoke <a href="javascript:card_browser(337)">Xyx</a></a>, <a href="javascript:card_browser(386)">Scroll of Fire</a> (or Last Words)<br>
<br>
Creatures<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(536)">Braggle</a> 3x<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(675)">Smoke <a href="javascript:card_browser(337)">Xyx</a></a> 3x<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(673)">Krawg</a> 3x<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(671)">Diomant</a> 3x<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(672}<a href="javascript:card_browser({516)">Gia</a>nt <a href="javascript:card_browser(394)">Arboll</a></a> 3x<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(537)">Er<a href="javascript:card_browser(377)">Gar</a></a> 3x<br>
Flame <a href="javascript:card_browser(404)">Rudwot</a> 3x<br>
<br>
Relics<br>
Robe oes 2x<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(787)">Rayje&#39;s Sword</a> 2x<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(545)">Blast Gloves</a> 3x<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(386)">Scroll of Fire</a> 2x<br>
The Last Words 1x<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(679}<a href="javascript:card_browser({378)">Grega</a>&#39;s Ring</a> 1x<br>
<br>
Spells<br>
Fireball 3x<br>
Brushfire 3x<br>
Crushing Heat 3x<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(393)">Thermal Blast</a> 3x<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(790)">Beam of Light</a> 3x<br>
<br>
Total : 47   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> I know what you&#39;re thinking. 47 cards! That&#39;s insane! However, it&#39;s very easy to downgrade this deck. Most of the cards are tripled, you can take out one or two here, or remove three of a creature, and so on. I don&#39;t, because I never have a problem with larger decks, and EVERY card in this deck has multiple uses.<br>
<br>
This deck revolves around cald spell-slinging. Brushfire, Fireball, and Thermal Blast can all be devastating to opposing creatures and magi, especially with Blast Gloves lying around. Very large creatures can be weakened, and then finished off with Vorga&#39;s Shatter, a well-cast Beam of Light, or other options.<br>
<br>
So here&#39;s the card-by-card thinkout.<br>
<br>
Magi :<br>
<br>
Barak the Red.<br>
I love this guy. Energy, Energy, Energy. Whenever I can, I choose to go second. This way, I can start pounding on opposing creatures. If Barak energizes, you&#39;ve got 22 energy to do that with. If you get stuck going first, he still has 17, enough to get a creature or two out, if you&#39;re nervous. His COMMAND power is very nice when you&#39;ve got an unnecessary card in your hand and you want to pull out any creature.<br>
<br>
Grega.<br>
A low starting energy, which is why she&#39;s never first in the deck. Barak usually lasts a long time, and you&#39;ve got many creatures and spells in your hand for when Grega comes out. She has a cheaper, built-in Thermal Blast power, as well as Grega&#39;s ring, which will let you thermal blast twice a round without spells. Don&#39;t be afraid to use the ring, even if you roll low with it, you still get to damage creatures before you lose it.<br>
<br>
Vorga.<br>
13/5, so she has 18 when she comes out. Starts with a scroll of fire, Smoke Xyx, and an arbolit. Her Shatter power is like a better Beam of Light, letting you kill off 3 energy or less creatures or annoying relics out there. Shatter is perfect when your thermal blast doesn&#39;t roll high enough, or when your opponent has many low-energy creatures.<br>
<br>
Spells:<br>
<br>
Beam of Light.<br>
I love this card. Kills annoying relics in play, finishes off weakened creatures, cancels spells like Corrupt. My opponents are always frustrated when thier key relics are destroyed.<br>
<br>
Thermal Blast.<br>
Paying 3, for a possible 1-6 damage. I usually cast these when I have a Scroll of Fire out, to minimize the chance i&#39;ll do only one or two damage. There&#39;s usually a creature out you can kill off with a single casting, and don&#39;t forget, it can target magi, too. More often than not, I wind up using this spell in conjunction with Blast Gloves to take out big creatures.<br>
<br>
Crushing Heat.<br>
Paying 4, for 4 damage to a creature, and a nifty little effect on the side. Kill a creature with this, and they&#39;re prevented from using the more useful relics out there.<br>
<br>
Brushfire.<br>
Paying 2 for 2 damage. When used with a Scroll of Fire in play, you&#39;re spending energy wisely. Once you play one, you can play it from your discard on every turn for the rest of the game.<br>
<br>
Fireball.<br>
The simplest of spells. Pay 2 for 2 damage, creature or magi. Again, use scroll of fire/blast gloves to make it stronger.<br>
<br>
Relics.<br>
<br>
Grega&#39;s Ring.<br>
Only one in the deck, and that&#39;s all you need. With it, Grega can thermal blast twice on her first turn, damaging potentially large opposing creatures and whittling down reserve energy on opposing magi. Try not to roll a one or two on it, and you&#39;re set. Consider pulling cards and adding Loaded Dice, if you&#39;re too nervous.<br>
<br>
Rayje&#39;s Sword.<br>
Added to the deck after my friend&#39;s Underneath deck gave me headaches. Counters annoying things like Burrow. Works to hurt your creatures too, but it&#39;s worth it, to me.<br>
<br>
Robes of the Ages.<br>
A card easily removed if you feel the deck is too large, but it&#39;s also very very efficient. With this and a scroll of fire in play, your fireballs/brushfires only cost 1 energy and do 3 damage. <br>
<br>
Blast Gloves.<br>
Discard it after you play a spell to double the damage removed by that spell. Excellent for doubling thermal blasts. Useable in multiplayer games, as well, since it can double any player&#39;s spells. Think teamwork.<br>
<br>
Scroll of Fire/The Last Words.<br>
Powers up your cald spells. I rarely use The Last Words since you can&#39;t discard energy from opposing magi, but the energy advantage is greater.<br>
<br>
Creatures.<br>
(on a side note, the majority of these creatures have spell-like powers. They all fit in well with the deck&#39;s theme.)<br>
<br>
Braggle.<br>
Incredibly useful. It&#39;s Morph ability will allow it to survive things like an Ormagon&#39;s Devastate, and will also let you attack without losing energy. I only wish morph was permanent, but nothing&#39;s perfect.<br>
<br>
Smoke Xyx.<br>
Suffocate lets your creatures attack opposing creatures without fear of retribution. Keep in mind, Smoke Xyx, too, can benefit from his own ability.<br>
<br>
Krawg.<br>
One of the few creatures that can be removed with no regrets. I had him in when I was using Good Ol&#39; Ashgar, and he IS nice for drawing cards. He&#39;s also one of the deck&#39;s few larger creatures, and his Immunity&#39;s nice.<br>
<br>
Diomant.<br>
A very nice critter. As long as he&#39;s alive with one energy, you can do four damage to an opposing magi. What I usually wind up doing is playing him, transferring five energy back to my magi, and using his Flame Hunt. Net result is, I only pay 1 energy to do 4 to the other magi.<br>
<br>
Giant Arboll.<br>
Virtually everything this deck does, also adds energy to Giant Arboll. Since he can also transfer all his energy back to you, or to another creature, he&#39;s essentially free. I usually play him before I cast a host of spells, then I heal up a creature or heal myself back up. He works amazingly well in conjunction with Ergar&#39;s effect...<br>
<br>
Ergar.<br>
Spark! Spark spark spark. every creature in play gets thier own little fireballs. with a scroll of fire out, a creature pays one to do 2 damage to creature or magi. if you have a large amount of creatures out, and a giant arboll, giant arboll&#39;s energy will skyrocket, then he&#39;ll heal something else. One of the better combo&#39;s of this deck.<br>
<br>
Flame Rudwot.<br>
Esentially, you pay 4 energy for him, then he does six energy worth of powers. (heal one of your creatures for 3, burn one of thier creatures for 3).<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
This is my first deck I&#39;m posting. I&#39;d like to point out just once more, hammer it home, that the deck can easily be only 40 cards. I just don&#39;t have a problem with it being big.<br>
<br>
Some things I&#39;d like to change are the fact that usually I only get 2 cards a turn, IE, my draw step. I&#39;m not sure how I can do that in a Cald Deck... Plus, there&#39;s other cald magi i&#39;ve tried. I&#39;ve settled on these three because of thier printed effects. Barak can find creatures, and vorga&#39;s ability is so useful, I use it almost every turn.<br>
<br>
Please, if you&#39;re going to criticize, make it constructive. I&#39;m willing to adapt the deck, but not change it severely. It wins a LOT where I play, and that&#39;s what counts to me =) </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/magination/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=24532"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=24532" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/magination/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></td></tr></table></td>
        </tr>
